          "text": "This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user invoked `/fix 1044` to analyze and fix GitHub issue #1044 in the ledger C++ accounting project. The issue reports that forecast doesn't respect `from`/`since` in period expressions — `until` works but `from`/`since` doesn't. The user wants the fix committed (with author `johnw@newartisans.com`), a regression test added, and a PR created targeting `main` on the `ledger/ledger` GitHub repo using the `jwiegley` GitHub user.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Ledger's forecast system: `forecast_posts` class generates synthetic future postings from periodic transactions (`~ Monthly`, `~ Weekly from ...`)\n   - `forecast_posts::add_post()` initializes intervals via `find_period(CURRENT_DATE())` — the bug location\n   - `forecast_posts::flush()` iterates pending posts, using `next` (not `start`) as the date for each forecast posting, effectively skipping the first period\n   - `date_interval_t::find_period()` calls `stabilize()` then checks if `date < *start` — returns false when CURRENT_DATE is before the period's `from` date\n   - `date_interval_t::stabilize()` sets `aligned = true` and initializes `start` from the range's begin date even when the reference date is before it\n   - `generate_posts::add_post()` stores a copy of the interval by value — the subsequent advancement loop in `forecast_posts::add_post()` modifies only a local copy (effectively dead code)\n   - Pre-commit hooks run cmake + build + ctest (4000+ tests) + doxygen + nix build (~8 min total)\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n   - **`src/filters.cc`** (lines 1834-1867) — Contains the bug fix in `forecast_posts::add_post()`. The original code silently dropped periodic transactions with future `from`/`since` dates because `find_period(CURRENT_DATE())` returned false. The fix detects